      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest in the validation activity must be directly relevant to the clinical decision quantity (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is relative hemolysis index RH derived from scalar stress accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law). This directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion RH < 1 relative to predicate device. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, velocity profiles) provide mechanistic traceability."
    },
    {
